profile_positions.description:
·	Managing a team of professionals responsible for both tax compliance and tax advisory;
·	Direct report to JV CFO, preparation of management information including JV’s tax position and tax forecasts;
·	Leading tax litigation (all levels), representing the company in the court;
·	Tax planning (VAT refund, corporate income tax structuring, etc);
·	Review of contracts from the tax perspective;
.      Accountability for equity (tax) reporting (tax line items – current and deferred tax);
·	Implementation of tax policies and procedures (tax accounting policy, cost allocation policy, deferred tax calculation procedures, etc);
·	Coordination of tax audits, communication with the high level tax authorities in Moscow and Nefteyugansk;
·	Coordination of external advisors;
·	Overall advisory on tax matters, final tax sign-off.

Development assignment in Shell EP Rijswijk. 

Responsible for overall compliance of the Upstream tax reporting with relevant financial accounting standards, including SOX 404;
- Review quarter-end tax charge for Shell Upstream (actual and latest estimates)
- Review annual tax charge in comparison with competitors;
- Act as a center of expertise for financial accounting matters in general;
Provided input of key tax assumption to overal Upstream business plan.

·	Supervision of tax compliance (monthly, quarterly and annual) of Shell Group companies including expatriates’ personal income tax compliance;
·	Consulting/advising other departments/companies on the Russian tax matters including new business development projects; 
·	Review of contracts/transactions from the tax point of view;
·	Implementation of Section 404 of Sarbanes-Oxley Act in Tax, including participation in controls testing outside of Russia (Shell Germany); 
·	Communications with the tax authorities, including tax audits and tax letigations;
·	Communication with external consultants and auditors;
·	Development of tax accounting policy;
·	Monitoring and implementations of applicable changes in the tax legislations;
·	Development of tax efficient cost allocation mechanism in the region.
